2026-05-03T23:37:57.5470318Z             "body": "## Summary\nThis PR adds a convenient shell script for running the web application locally with configurable logging and branch switching capabilities.\n\n## Key Changes\n- **Added `run-web.sh`**: A new bash script that simplifies local development by:\n  - Pulling the latest changes from the current branch\n  - Optionally switching to a specified branch before running\n  - Configuring logging levels via environment variables\n  - Supporting `--trace` flag to enable debug logging for the application\n  - Supporting `--no-mask` flag to disable trace masking when tracing is enabled\n  - Running the Ednsv.Web project via `dotnet run`\n\n- **Updated CI workflow**: Modified `.github/workflows/ci.yml` to ignore `*.sh` files in the paths-ignore configuration, preventing unnecessary CI runs when only shell scripts are modified\n\n## Implementation Details\n- The script uses standard bash argument parsing with a case statement to handle `--trace`, `--no-mask`, and `--branch` options\n- Logging is configured through environment variables following the ASP.NET Core configuration pattern\n- Default logging level is set to Information, with Microsoft.AspNetCore warnings suppressed\n- When trace mode is enabled, both Program and Ednsv.Web loggers are set to Debug level\n- The script exits on any error with `set -e` for safety\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_019LKaQKQrt4u2pdAqnoyQon",
